HEADWORD: nonretractile
<hw>nonretractile</hw></mhw>
<pos>adj.</pos> <def>not able to be drawn into the main body; -- of
claws and other extensile parts of animals or objects; <as>as, a bear's
claws, unlike a cat's, are <ex>nonretractile</ex></as>. Opposite of
<ant>retractile</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

